FOOT AND MOUTH DISEASE - NAMIBIA (02): (OTJOZONDJUPA) BUFFALO,
CONFIRMED, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
*************************************************************************************************

A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 7 Sep 2011
Source: AllAfrica, New Era report [summ., edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201109071061.html


Residents of Okakarara [Otjozondjupa Region] have been hit where it
hurts most. They are not allowed to sell their cattle that are their
main source of income because of the current 21-day quarantine on
cattle.

The Ministry of Agriculture effected the quarantine after 2 buffaloes
that tested positive for the contagious foot-and-mouth disease (FMD)
had to be put down.

"People in the 5 settlements are affected. Their pockets are empty,"
said Okakarara Constituency councillor, Vetaruhe Kandorozu, adding
that there was almost no alternative other than selling chicken and
vegetables -- something the farmers are not "intensive on".

Kandorozu said that farmers typically sell one herd of cattle every
month or so and depend on auctions for finances. This, he said, would
also affect schools as they may not receive fees until the quarantine
has been lifted.

The livestock movement restriction runs until 20 Sep 2011, but it is
not clear what would happen after that. "There is no income now.
Individual businesses are starting to feel the pinch too," added the
councillor.

The Okakarara Trade Fair (OTF), which starts today [7 Sep 2011], is
also expected to take a blow as gate entrance intake may be affected.

Veterinary Services director Dr Cleophas Bamhare said they were doing
surveillance in the area and would reassess the situation after the 21
days lapse.

A man was gored in the stomach by one of the 2 buffaloes, whose blood
samples revealed a positive result for FMD. The buffaloes were spotted
in Ekuenje, some 20 km [12.5 mi] from Okondjatu.

[Byline: Magreth Nunuhe]

