[According to the initial report on the event, on 29 Aug 2011 no
results of the lab tests of the 2 suspected buffaloes were yet
available (see ProMED-mail 20110901.2675). As it appears now, the 2
animals, sighted within the Otjozondjupa region, one of the 8 regions
within the recognised FMD-free zone of Namibia, have eventually been
found infected/positive. Details of the test applied will be helpful.

Animal movement restrictions and surveillance have been implemented in
order to protect Namibia's status as a country maintaining a zone free
of FMD without vaccination. Such status is meant to provide Namibia
the potential of gaining access to a wide range of national and
international markets. The zone includes the regions of Kunene south,
Oshikoto south, Otjozondjupa, Omaheke, Khomas, Erongo, Hardap, and
Karas (see map and additional details at
http://www.nammic.com.na/pdf/Foot_Mouthdisease.pdf). - Mod.AS]

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Namibia can be seen at
http://healthmap.org/r/1dDw. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
